=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_EnvGen_ex7 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright clean sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 50 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, and filtered with steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: clean
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -2.9500
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9468
  pitch_clarity: 106.4649
  inharmonicity: 0.0263
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -17.3984
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: EnvGen Example 7
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/EnvGen.html
// Tags: EnvGen, Classes, envelope
// ---
// --- Example 7 ---
(
// a Synth with a multi-node release stage
d = { |gate = 1|
    var env = Env([0, 1, 0, 0.5, 0], 0.5, -4, releaseNode: 1);
    { BrownNoise.ar }.dup * EnvGen.kr(env, gate, doneAction: Done.freeSelf)
}.play;
)
// forced release in 2 seconds:
// end value (0) and shape (-4) are read from the env's last node, nodes 2 and 3 are skipped
d.release(2);

// without releaseTime: normal release stage, as defined in env (3 nodes)
d.release();
